transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks a lot Viagra, Quinn speaking. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I need to cancel an order and any future orders associated with my name please.

Speaker 1: Is your name Craig?

Speaker 2: It is.

Speaker 1: One moment.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Oh yeah, I do see you are a VIP here with the circuit and Viagra.

Speaker 2: Do you mind if I ask why you're canceling?

Speaker 1: Because I didn't order it. My brother did that as a prank the other night.

Speaker 2: And then he told me about it after he did it.

Speaker 1: Sorry, you said that you didn't order it?

Speaker 2: My brother did it as a prank.

Speaker 1: Oh, that's an expensive prank.

Speaker 2: No joke.

Speaker 1: He got a kick out of it, let me tell you.

Speaker 2: Yeah, okay. Well, as soon as you ship that back to us we can go ahead and give you a refund for that.

Speaker 1: And I want to make sure there's not any future orders that are going to be coming to my attention either.

Speaker 2: And you are aware you can order this as needed if you want to, correct?

Speaker 1: But I don't need it. I said it was a prank.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that's hard to...

Speaker 1: That is a hard one, sir.

Speaker 2: Alright, we'll go ahead and take care of it for you.

Speaker 1: Alright, I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: Will I get an email confirmation or something to tell me it's canceled?

Speaker 1: No, sir. Just a verbal one that your prescription is canceled.

Speaker 2: Okay, that's fine. As long as I don't get any more shipments.

Speaker 1: And then you said this other one's already shipped, so I'll send it back.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Alright, I appreciate your help.

Speaker 2: Yeah.
